body:
@romisalve How were you able to unlock the geth node perpetually? It looks like Q Maker uses an older version of `geth` that doesn't have the `--allow-insecure-unlock` flag so the node appears to lock up after the default 300s.

What was your error for the large contract? IIRC, Quorum has a super large block gas limit so I'm surprised you ran into that type of error. Can you share a link to your contract?

Regarding the ABI, I'm not sure yet on the scope of Q Maker, but if you're able to provide reproducible steps (i.e. link to a repo) I can take a look.
